@node MAIN_SPECS "PuzzleBOBS guide - Technical specs"

Technical specs
---------------


  PuzzleBOBS is inspired to the lucky game rooms puzzle game series and introduces a lot of new
characteristics as the asynchronous game style, the possibility of playing two players mode
simultaneously in the same level, and the ability of accept a lot of levelsets with dissimilar
features.
  Moreover this game is totally configurable: you could choose screen-mode by a system requester
(supported AGA, ECS, OCS and graphic expansions as PicassoIV or Cybervision or others which are
AmigaOS compatibles by Picasso96 or CyberGraphX) up to 16-24 bits colour, all the graphical
elements of game as fonts, lateral columns, rotating pointer with gears, bubbles (of each size,
color, form, and number also animated up to 255 frames), backgrounds, then you can choose the
speed of moving objects, music and fx-sounds, apperances of explosions (as frames per seconds,
by gfx or a CPU precalculated animation), and a lot of other lowlevel options as the behaviour of
artificial brains and priorities of game's subtasks.
  Thanks to the polyvalence of LevelSet files subsystem you can have various behaviour of bubbles
in game, for example some which rebound against the top limit increasing the difficulty of game or
disposed in level by four or six tangents.
  Moreover the game foresees a lot of special bubbles as three type of bombs and others.
  PuzzleBOBS allows to zoom the bubbles if can not fit them into the level so you can use a lot of
levels even very big without space problems, or force a default zoom to save a lot of video mem.
  The game works in multitasking and can be played further on a screen so in a Workbench's window
also in a PIP (if your board affords that).
  The game can go in manual pause (p) crypting the level or can go in sleep mode automatically when
the screen or window became inactives, in the same time frees the audio channels and if you was
using a window remaps the workbench's palette.
  The hiscore system allows to maintain a lot of information about the score so you will be able to
remember the date, the LevelSet used, the game mode, the number of players, the difficulty of that
past match.
  The game has a built-in subsystem that is able to simulate the blitter's work (on VGA, AGA, ECS,
OCS) putting all graphic data (bitmaps) in fast mem (the only chip mem used is the screen's mem)
and increasing a lot the speed of Amiga without graphic board (need some fastmem).
  The game is based on a particular architecture which uses deeply the AmigaOs multitasking
characteristichs. Infact it uses a lot of sub tasks (of which you can set the priority) each one
assigned to a game's operation.
  For example there is a task which controls rotations, one which draws bobs animation and others
which controls players, levels, controllers, explosions etc, etc, these communicate between them
with signals and messages.
  The game was developed on an Amiga A4000T 68040 25MHZ, written totally in assembler. It consists
of 1.3 MBytes of code (about 70000 lines of sources). The developing started during the summer of
1997.



@endnode

@node MAIN_SCOPO "PuzzleBOBS guide - Game's target"

Game's target
-------------

  The game target is to clear all the bubbles in the screen, they explode when near in a group of
three minimum, or fall down because free from others exploded. When you erase them all you pass to
a new level.
  To launch the bubble you have to press fire button, to choose its direction you have to keep the
aim moving the pointer in the bottom of the screen.
  Remember that there is a time limit between two launchs, counted by a small timer displayed
near the pointer. When the count down arrives to zero the bubble will be launched automatically.
  Moreover after some launchs all the group of bubbles will be moved down. If a bubble go over the
level limit stripe the game is over and you have to start again from the first one.
  The same for a bubble you launch from your pointer, even if placed would explode some bubbles upon
the limit.
  Each time you erase some bubbles you get some score, depending the difficulty level you choosed,
more it is harder, more score you get.
  The LevelSets could be various, they may be time limited, they could have various dispositions of
bubbles, as at four or six tangents.
  PuzzleBOBS foresees various game modes, the first one is the normal, in which you play alone.
  The same could be faced by the cooperation of two players, the cooperative method, you will have
two pointers and in the same time you will be able to attack the same group of bubbles.
  The advantage is to play in pair and if a player mistakes putting a bubble under the level limit
forget the fire faculty, but gaining again its in the level after if the second player is able to
finish the previous one.
  Finally two players can challenge using the competitive method, in which each player has a own
level with the same group of bubbles of its opponent. Who for first clear the level wins.
  Lose who puts a bubble under the level limit stripe. A bubble which falls is sent to the opponent
level group of bubbles.



@endnode

