@NODE i_start "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Start"

Start
-----

  Starts the game, using all the options expressed in the menu.
 
@ENDNODE

@NODE i_gamemode "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Game mode"

Game mode
---------
 
  Here you choose the game mode. It may be NORMAL, COOPERATIVE or COMPETITIVE. Choosing the NORMAL
mode you play alone to all levels.
  The same could be faced by the cooperation of two players, by the COOPERATIVE method, you will have
two pointers and in the same time you will be able to attack the same group of bubbles.
  The advantage is to play in pair and if a player mistakes putting a bubble under the level limit
forget the fire faculty, but gaining again its in the level after if the second player is able to
finish the previous one.
  Finally two players can challenge using the COMPETITIVE method, in which each player has a own
level with the same group of bubbles of its opponent. Who for first clear the level wins.
  Lose who puts a bubble under the level limit stripe. A bubble which falls is sent to the opponent
level group of bubbles.

 

@ENDNODE
@NODE i_difficulty "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Difficulty"

Difficulty
----------

  By this option you may decide the difficulty of game. The difficulty is based on the reduction
of bob's shade used to detect collisions.
  More the game is easier more the shade is reduced, and more results easy to launch a bob, 
because a lot of collisions events are bypassed.
  When you play with the hard setting the shade respects the real bob surface, so the collisions
detection becames more and more precise and the game harder.


@ENDNODE
@NODE i_incontri "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Matches"

Matches
-------

  Her you choose the number of matches to play during the @{" COMPETITIVE " LINK i_gamemode} game mode.
  A player wins the challenge when wins 1, 2 of 3, 3 of 5, 4 of 7 matches.

@ENDNODE
@NODE i_giocatori "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Players"

Players
-------

  Here you choose how many players will play, you can be alone or you can play with a friend
using the various @{" game modes " LINK i_gamemode}.
  

@ENDNODE
@NODE i_tipi "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Player 1 - Player 2"

Player 1 - Player 2
-------------------

  You choose if the player is HUMAN or non human (AMIGA).
  The artificial player could be choosed, read about the @{" AI " LINK i_configai} menu page.

@ENDNODE
@NODE i_controllers "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Controllers"

Controllers
-----------

  By this option you enter in a sub page dedicated to game's input controllers, foresee: Mouse,
Joystick, JoyPad and Keyboard.
  Here you can choose the controller for each player and moreover the computer port to which it 
is connected.	
  The port 0 is the one to which usually is connected the mouse.


@ENDNODE
@NODE i_configai "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Config AI"

Config AI
---------

  By this option you can enter in the artificial intelligence (AI) configuration sub page. There
you can define the aspects of the two artificial players. PuzzleBOBS AI sub system allows a large
range of different artificials players, each one with several characteristics and abilities.
  An AI is defined by an "AI Configuration File", an ASCII editable file, which contains some
informations about.
  
  >Choose Ai 1
   By this option you get a File Requester by which you can pick an AI Configuration File.
   This define the first artificial brain.

  >Choose Ai 2
   By this option you get a File Requester by which you can pick an AI Configuration File.
   This define the second artificial brain.

  >Abouts Ai 1 and 2 Informations
   By this option you can get informations stored in the AI Configuration File, as the name and
   author of Config file, and some comments about the defined AI.
 

@ENDNODE
