@NODE i_pointer "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Misc/Pointer"

Pointer
-------

  You can disable the mouse pointer rendering during the game (ON/OFF), if you play in a window
this will be not disabled.
  


@ENDNODE
@NODE i_palette "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Misc/Palette"

Palette
-------

  If you play in window you can choose, when the window becames inactive or if you go in pause, if
restore the WorkBench`s screen palette or not.
  

@ENDNODE
@NODE i_zoomrespect "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Misc/Zoom Respect"

Zoom Respect
------------

  When you play to levels which are too big, the bobs will be zoomed to be fitted in the smaller
space. If you set this option to ON you will have bob scaled respecting their original sizes, else
you will get various scaled bobs depending on space allowed.


@ENDNODE
@NODE i_sleepwindow "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Misc/Sleep window"

Sleep window
------------

  If you set this to ON, when your screen or window becames inactive the game goes, without use the
pause key ( p ), in sleep mode automatically, otherwise the game will continue its action.
  Remember that if you use the keyboard as game controller, the Workbench's preferences settings
about key's delays and ripetition speed will be modified during the game phase, and only setting
this option to ON you get preferences restored to old values, during screen swapping.
  When you press the "p" key to enter in pause or your screen or window became inactive, PuzzleBOBS
will free the allocated audio channels also.


@ENDNODE
@NODE i_fastexit "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Misc/Fast exit"

Fast exit
---------

  If you set this to ON when you press "esc" during the game stage you will escape directly,
otherwise if you set this to OFF the game will ask you by a message if you want really exit from
game.
  If you press again the "esc" you will confirm the escape, while with an other keyboard's key you
ask to continue your game stage.

 

@ENDNODE
@NODE i_movenext "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Misc/Move next"

Move next
---------
  
  You can choose at which speed you want the next bob to be moved over the pointer. By FAST you will
disable the animation movement so it will be moved in the faster way possible, by SLOW you ask the
animation.
  However the speed of movement could be deeply configured directly in the ConfigFile under the
"Ball Movements" chapter.

@ENDNODE
@NODE i_extradata "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Misc/Extra data"

Extra data
----------

  There are some ConfigFiles which foresee some additionals graphics elements as new backgrounds,
palette and others. Here you can choose how sort them sequentially.
 	  
  >Random
   By this option you pick one of them via random.
	
  >Sequence
   You pick the new one in sequence, so one for each level.
	
  >Shared
   You get them considering the LevelSet's levels number, so you divide their number by the levels
   number. If you have a 30 levels LevelSet and 3 different graphic sets you will change them every
   10 levels.
		
  >Disable
   You disable the extra data, so you will play with the first set only, the one displayed during
   menu.


@ENDNODE
@NODE i_aslrequester "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Misc/Asl reqs"

Asl reqs
--------

  PuzzleBOBS uses asl requesters to allow you, for example, to choose files and screen resolutions.
  Unsfortunately on some systems asl requesters may give some problems, they may leave trails when
moved or closed. For this reason the default option is set to "Open Out", so all asl requester will 
be open on Workbench's screen.
  If you want to have asl requester on the PuzzleBOBS own screen you can choose the "Open In"
option, but verify if on your configuration you get the above problems.  


@ENDNODE
@NODE i_hiscores "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Misc/Hiscores"

Hiscores
--------

  You can set to ON or OFF the hiscore system, if set to ON when you enter in the ten best results
the game will ask you your name, else with OFF you disable the hiscore recognition.

@ENDNODE

@NODE i_audio "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Audio"

Audio
-----

  PuzzleBOBS accepts various setups about the audio, a lot of them are visibles in this page. The
audio on Amiga platform is generated by 4 differents and indipendents voices, or channels. An
application or task which want use the audio output can choose to use one or more channels.
  PuzzleBOBS allocates a number of channels equal to your menu's settings, so you can decide how
many channels using during the game, but if a channel is busy because an other task is using its
it will be not considered, and PuzzleBOBS will allocates only the other free channels. If no 
channel is free, the audio will not be generated, but however the game will start.
  In the menu you have a lot of free choices about samples and musics output, you may change them,
but to apply the changes you have to use the menu "apply" voice.
  By this action, you will get the status of your system capabilities, so if you ask four channels
and the system is just using two of them you will see the channels voices to go to two channels
status, and if is not possible to have the Audio3D effect its voice will be set to OFF.
  Remember that if you activate the music you lose 3 or all the channels. So is possible to listen
music and sfx effects in the same time but with 3 channels for musics and only one channel for
 effects. In this case the Audio3D is disabled.

 
