@ENDNODE
@NODE i_musicacanali "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Audio/Music chans"

Music chans
-------------
  
  Is possible to choose how many channels alloc to render the musics. You can enable 0, 3, or 4
channels. If you enable 3 channels the game will use e decode system which leaves a channel to the
samples, but which has a lower output quality respect the 4 channels mode.
  Enable 0 chans looks like put to OFF the @{" Music " LINK i_musica} voice.
   


@ENDNODE
@NODE i_sfx "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Audio/Sfx"

Sfx
---

  Enable or disable (ON/OFF) sound samples output.

@ENDNODE

@NODE i_sfxcanali "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Audio/Sfx chans"

Sfx chans
---------

  With this option you can choose how many channels are used to play the audio effects. If 
PuzzleBOBSB can't open all the channels, will try to render the audio only with the avaibles.
 If all channles are busy, the audio will be disabled. You can disable the samples output choosing
0 channels also.
  
 
@ENDNODE

@NODE i_audio3d "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Audio/Audio3D"

Audio3D
-------

  With this option you can toggle the space effect. If enabled PuzzleBOBS will output a sample
considering the event on screen. If the event happens in the left middle of screen, PB will try
to render its on the left two channels, if can not bacause they aren't avaibles because busy will 
render its on the right two channels. To be enabled PuzzleBOBS needs almost one channels for both
sides, left and right. 


@ENDNODE
@NODE i_modo "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Audio/Mode"

Mode
----

  You can choose four various settings, ASYNCHRO, SYNCHRO, ABORTLAST, GOAWAY. When an event needs
an audio output asks a channel to be output, but can happens that all channels are busy, for this
reason you can:

  >SYNCHRO
   Wait, and when a channel became free output the effect, so you get a precise audio output
   when an event happens, but this could stop your event for a while.

  >ASYNCHRO
   Don't wait a channel became free, you ask a channel but you continue your action, in this way
   your events will not be stopped, but can happens that the audio effect starts in delay, so
   you may lost the cause/effect. 

  >ABORTLAST
   The third is a mixture of two above method, because you ask a channel, and if is not free an
   other past request will be stopped to be replaced with this new one.
   This method don't stop the action and dont' delay the output effect, but can stop a past
   effect truncing the sample output. 
 
  >GOAWAY
   The last method aborts the output of a sample if there is no free channels.
   By this method the events are not stopped but can happens that some effects are not 
   outputed loosing them.

  Is important to say that probably the best choice is ABORTLAST, because you will get always a
sample output when an event occurs. Is also real that this method can became inefficent when
samples became longer and longer, for this reason the best is try your samples set with all the
choices in the menu, because for example if you are using a sample set with very short effects
could be good to use the SYNCRHO choice also.

@ENDNODE

@NODE i_applica "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Audio/Apply"

Apply
-----
  
  Use this option to test the status of your system. PuzzleBOBS will try to alloc all channels you
asked, but if there are some channels busy because requested by an other app you will get enabled
only the available modes.
  If you want the musics you need 3 channels minimum. If you use 4 channels you can not listen sfx
effects and enable the Audio3D. If you use 3 channels for musics you can enable the samples but
using a channel only. Even in this case the Audio3D is disabled.



@ENDNODE

@NODE i_aprisamples "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Audio/Load samples"

Load samples
------------

