@NODE i_blitmode "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Configure/Blit mode"

Blit mode
---------

  By this option you can choose which functions you want to use to render the graphic. Be careful,
some of them could leave imperfections on video or render badly the graphic.
  I suggest to read the @{" Graphic procedures " LINK MAIN_GFXF} page in which you can find more
infos about this modes.
  The default option is "Blit mode = Use OS". 
	  
  >Use OS
   This uses the Os graphic function, and is very suggested when you use a graphic board, while on
   standard Amiga screens could be better choose "Blit mode = Cpu fast". 
 	
  >Use HW
   This uses some Os functions in combination with other optimized functions. This mode could work
   badly leaving imperfections on screen. 		

  >Cpu chip
   This mode uses the CPU instead of Blitter in all circumstances, but continue to work in chip
   memory, so could be very slow, need very fast processors.

  >Cpu fast
   This is as "Cpu chip" because uses the Cpu instead of Blitter but works with data in fast memory
   (Public mem), so is very fast and compatible with the Os.
   On graphic boards could cause some problems, as imperfections on screen, so is better in this
   case use the "Use OS" option.
	 
  >Cpu+blitter
   This mode uses Blitter and Cpu in the same time, so part of Blit will be done by the Blitter,
   and the rimanent by the Cpu.
   Moreover in ConfigFiles there is a value with which you can choose in percentage how part of
   blit have to be done by the Blitter, the rimanent will be done by the Cpu at the same time.
   The default ConfigFile percentage is 50%. This mode is disabled when using a graphic board's
   screen mode (uses "Os funcs").




