@NODE i_buffer "PuzzleBOBS guide - Menu/Configure/More/Buffer"

Buffer
------

  This option can be set to "Single" or to "Multiple" and is usefull only when are playing two
players at the same time. Infact if you choose the "Multiple" mode the game will allocate a very
big buffer (needed by the game to make a lot of graphical operations, as clipping) for each
player, else if you use the "Single" mode you will get only one buffer used by two player at the 
same time.
  The fastest mode is "Multiple" because a player to draw in a buffer doesn't have to wait the
other one have finished, so has an own private buffer, but,	as disadvantage, needs a larger
request of memory, which is doubled.
  However this options set to "Multiple" increase a lot the performances of game in all its
aspects, as for example, the bobs explosions.
  


